# Image sanitisation for the staff-managed inspiration catalogue (Phase 5B):
# decode-verify, EXIF strip, resize and WebP re-encode. The ONLY image
# dependency — no ImageMagick, no libmagic, no external processing services.
Pillow==11.3.0
# Structured DesignSpec contract (Phase 8): a strict Pydantic v2 model is the
# authoritative shape of generated design specifications and the source of the
# committed JSON Schema. Sitara uses Pydantic directly, so it is an explicit
# direct dependency (not merely an Anthropic transitive).
pydantic==2.13.4
# Anthropic structured-output client for gated DesignSpec generation (Phase 8).
# Provider calls are fail-closed: a present key never enables a call, tests
# inject a fake client, and CI never instantiates a real network client.
anthropic==0.116.0
# Replicate client for gated FLUX image rendering (Phase 10). Same fail-closed
# discipline as Anthropic: a present token never enables a call, the client is
# created lazily only after every gate passes, tests inject fakes, and CI never
# reaches Replicate (socket-denied). Only public async-prediction SDK
# interfaces are used (no replicate.run(), no experimental replicate.use()).
replicate==1.0.7

